Overall, I liked this concept. It is intriguing and interesting. I had to downvote it, however, for two reasons. First off, there is a considerable amount of technological lingo (aka technobabble) that I just wasn't able to follow. Try to tone it down some, or just go into a more detailed explanation of what it means using simpler terms. TL;DR: Dumb it down.

My second issue, which will be harder to fix, is that the tone is just all wrong. You have this written more like a narrative; if you want to discuss the history of the object, add a "discovery" section. As well, talking about how a new researcher came and saved the day is just a bit silly and superfluous. The description should only be information that someone new to the object would need to handle it effectively.

So yeah, overall I liked it but downvoted for the aforementioned reasons. If you can fix those up I may switch my vote. Good luck!







